                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "IMO, this (determining whether the right fields were submitted) is part of form validation and should be the responsibility of the application, not the framework.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-05T23:30:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-05T23:30:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49934",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I concur with Adam. If there's a possibility of multiple forms, or forms targeted at different actions of the same request, you should be namespacing them -- usually this is done by grouping all fields of a form under the form's name (\"login[user]\", \"login[password]\" vs \"comment[subject]\", \"comment[body]\"). This is logic that you as a developer need to perform -- not the framework (though the framework enables this practice in Zend_Form).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-06T14:26:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-06T14:26:42.000+0000"
                }
            ]
